## Frontend ↔ Database Mapping

| Frontend Type | DB Table | Key Differences |
|---|---|---|
| [Bunk](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/types.ts#2-8) | `bunks` | `id` → UUID instead of string |
| [User](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/types.ts#9-16) | `users` + `user_bunk_access` | `password` → `password_hash`; `accessibleBunkIds[]` → junction table |
| [Account](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/types.ts#17-26) | `accounts` | Self-referencing `parent_id` FK; `createdAt` number → `timestamptz` |
| [Voucher](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/types.ts#27-37) | `vouchers` | [date](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/pages/DailyVoucher.tsx#89-101) string → `txn_date` DATE; added CHECK constraint |
| [LedgerEntry](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/types.ts#38-46) | *(computed view)* | Not stored — calculated from `accounts` + `vouchers` at query time |
| [Reminder](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/types.ts#47-56) | `reminders` | `createdAt` number → `timestamptz`; dates → proper DATE type |

---

## Design Notes

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **[LedgerEntry](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/types.ts#38-46) is NOT a table** — it's computed on-the-fly from `accounts` + `vouchers` using the [calculateLedger()](file:///c:/Users/Srivarmaa/Desktop/HK/KR-FUELS/utils.ts#27-65) function. You can create a PostgreSQL **view** or **function** for this if needed.

> [!WARNING]
> The frontend currently stores passwords in **plain text**. The schema uses `password_hash` — ensure your backend hashes with **bcrypt** or **argon2** before inserting.

> [!TIP]
> The `accounts` table is hierarchical (self-referencing `parent_id`). Use PostgreSQL **recursive CTEs** (`WITH RECURSIVE`) to traverse the tree for reports like the Accounts List page.
